<h2>Rene Bourdages</h2>
<h3>CEO<br />Elevado Media, Inc.</h3>
<div style="float: left;">
  <img src="/CES/media/2014/Conference/SpeakerHeadshots/Rene_Bourdages_Elevado-Media,-Inc.jpg?ext=.jpg" style="margin: 0px 15px 10px 0px; max-width: 275px;" alt="Rene Bourdages">
</div>
<div style="margin: 10px;">
  Rene Bourdages is a veteran entertainment executive with more than 30 years of senior level operating experience. Mr. Bourdages held many high level executive positions before focusing his managerial skills on entertainment media consulting in Canada and Los Angeles. He recently published INVESTING IN FILMS: The 12.5 Secrets Elite Investors Keep for Themselves. <br><br>http://www.amazon.com/Investing-Films-Individuals-Investments-Independent/dp/0692283013/ref=tmm_pap_title_0?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1415576869&amp;sr=8-1<br><br>Prior to founding Elevado Media, he was President of CBC (Canadian Broadcasting Corporation) merchandising from 2004 through 2011. He has also held Executive Vice President positions at Quebecor and Astral Media Movie Premium networks with direct responsibility for up to 1,200 employees and gross revenues of nearly $200 million. Previously, Mr. Bourdages served as Director of the Harold Greenberg Fund, which finances the development and production of Independent feature films.<br><br>He holds a Certificate in Business and Management of Entertainment from UCLA.&nbsp; He was selected as one of Canada’s Top 40 under 40.<br><br>Mr. Bourdages is a member of the Academy of Television Arts &amp; Sciences and the American Film Institute. <br><br>MAJOR ACCOMPLISHMENTS<br><br>•Responsible for the launch of two of Canada's most successful TV shows in recent history: Star Académie and Occupation Double.<br><br>•Grew network audience share to 39% in one year after directing the launch of many hit drama and variety shows.<br><br>•Spearheaded a new business unit, attaining $70 M in sales and garnering a Grammy Award win. <br><br>•Increased sales of a 20-year-old pay TV network by 38% in 2 years by negotiating 5-year distribution deal with satellite distributors and fully rebranding 3 distinct pay-TV services.<br><br>•Generated record sales on PPV, Pay, and conventional TV.<br><br>•Involved first-hand in negotiations with Major Studios and Foreign media and entertainment companies (UK, France, Greece, Portugal, Germany, Poland, Italy)
</div>



              
